code: @Override public void write(String executionName, PrintStream out, DataSet<T> data) throws Exception {     Collect<T> collector = new Collect<T>().run(data).     if (printExecutionPlan.getValue()) {         out.println().         out.println(data.getExecutionEnvironment().getExecutionPlan()).     }     List<T> results = collector.execute(executionName).     if (results.size() == 0) {         return.     }     out.println().     if (results.get(0) instanceof PrintableResult) {         for (Object result : results) {             out.println(((PrintableResult) result).toPrintableString()).         }     } else {         for (Object result : results) {             out.println(result).         }     } }
